target":"recEP3QZ3HUmIkv4Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec4eDKmyRHoXa15e","target":"recEoYRAyVeAancS0","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec4eDKmyRHoXa15e","target":"rec5dSSsOutWlH2fW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec4eDKmyRHoXa15e","target":"rec3JgMop7qtLBNCH","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec4eDKmyRHoXa15e","target":"recCh323mcqdG01EW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rechCkE909qPVuHCa","ref":"2Kgs.6.1","text":"And the sons of the prophets said unto Elisha, Behold now, the place where we dwell with thee is too strait for us.","year":-893},{"id":"rec2hQl5IP9ggWRsl","ref":"2Kgs.6.2","text":"Let us go, we pray thee, unto Jordan, and take thence every man a beam, and let us make us a place there, where we may dwell. And he answered, Go ye.","year":-893},{"id":"recPWS3nmUzb7lIXw","ref":"2Kgs.6.3","text":"And one said, Be content, I pray thee, and go with thy servants. And he answered, I will go.","year":-893},{"id":"recbVE6AfxhmqWiaW","ref":"2Kgs.6.4","text":"So he went with them. And when they came to Jordan, they cut down wood.","year":-893},{"id":"recEFSavqZ0JIuS4q","ref":"2Kgs.6.5","text":"But as one was felling a beam, the axe head fell into the water: and he cried, and said, Alas, master! for it was borrowed.","year":-893},{"id":"recRA6FQPAKI4qsoH","ref":"2Kgs.6.6","text":"And the man of God said, Where fell it? And he shewed him the place. And he cut down a stick, and cast it in thither; and the iron did swim.","year":-893},{"id":"recGWYQMAWJQL50FJ","ref":"2Kgs.6.7","text":"Therefore said he, Take it up to thee. And he put out his hand, and took it.","year":-893},{"id":"recbSNWrzFkTtck9b","ref":"2Kgs.6.8","text":"Then the king of Syria warred against Israel, and took counsel with his servants, saying, In such and such a place shall be my camp.","year":-893}]}
